{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DWAytCfq46mpDHL3pCzppQ","type":"tool_result","content":"363\t## Epic 4: Agent Dispatch & Session Management\n364\t\n365\tEngine spawns Claude Code sessions via Agent SDK with session boundaries, trace IDs, source isolation.\n366\t\n367\t### Story 4.1: Agent Dispatch Module — SDK Integration\n368\t\n369\tAs a developer,\n370\tI want an agent-dispatch module that spawns sessions via the Agent SDK,\n371\tSo that agent execution is programmatic and reliable.\n372\t\n373\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n374\t\n375\t**Given** a compiled subagent definition and a prompt\n376\t**When** `dispatchAgent()` is called\n377\t**Then** Agent SDK `query()` is invoked with bare: true\n378\t**And** function returns when session completes\n379\t**And** spawn completes in <5s excluding model response\n380\t**And** no child_process.spawn used for Claude CLI\n381\t**And** API limit, network, and binary-not-found errors handled gracefully\n382\t\n383\t### Story 4.2: Session Boundary Management\n384\t\n385\tAs a developer,\n386\tI want session boundaries configurable per task,\n387\tSo that context resets and continuity are controlled.\n388\t\n389\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n390\t\n391\t**Given** a task with session: fresh\n392\t**When** dispatched\n393\t**Then** a new SDK query is created with no resume/continue\n394\t**And** given session: continue, previous session ID is passed via resume\n395\t**And** session IDs tracked in workflow-state\n396\t\n397\t### Story 4.3: Trace ID Generation & Injection\n398\t\n399\tAs a developer,\n400\tI want trace IDs generated per iteration and injected into prompts,\n401\tSo that agent activity correlates to observability data.\n402\t\n403\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n404\t\n405\t**Given** an iteration starting\n406\t**When** a trace ID is generated\n407\t**Then** format is `ch-{runId}-{iteration}-{taskName}`\n408\t**And** injected into agent's system prompt via appendSystemPrompt\n409\t**And** recorded in workflow-state.yaml\n410\t\n411\t### Story 4.4: Source Isolation Enforcement\n412\t\n413\tAs a developer,\n414\tI want source_access: false enforced via source-free workspace,\n415\tSo that the evaluator cannot access implementation code.\n416\t\n417\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n418\t\n419\t**Given** a task with source_access: false\n420\t**When** the agent is dispatched\n421\t**Then** temp directory created with only story files\n422\t**And** SDK cwd set to temp directory\n423\t**And** disallowedTools: [Edit, Write] set on subagent\n424\t**And** src/ not present in workspace\n425\t\n426\t---\n427\t\n428\t## Epic 5: Workflow Execution Engine\n429\t\n430\t`codeharness run` executes workflows — per-story, per-run, loop blocks, finding injection, reads stories and issues.\n431\t\n432\t### Story 5.1: Flow Execution — Sequential Steps\n433\t\n434\tAs a developer,\n435\tI want the engine to execute flow steps sequentially,\n436\tSo that tasks run in defined order.\n437\t\n438\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n439\t\n440\t**Given** a resolved workflow with flow: [implement, verify]\n441\t**When** `codeharness run` executes\n442\t**Then** per-story tasks run first (one per story/issue)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015upEEv2DfZnR9xKiJz9ZsK","session_id":"84c2a87f-6818-4ede-b88c-dde16fd6e99b","uuid":"5951623e-ea74-4264-985c-ed5c8c81f96c","timestamp":"2026-04-02T19:28:15.733Z"}
