{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LDdrsra2VEHQcBL2x2nw5x","type":"tool_result","content":"34-- Cross-cutting concerns: config resolution chain, trace ID propagation, crash recovery, evaluator isolation\n35-\n36-### Technical Constraints & Dependencies\n37-\n38-- Runtime: Node.js (TypeScript)\n39:- Dependencies: `commander`, `yaml`, `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`\n40:- Execution substrate: Agent SDK `query()` — async generator, session management, JSON schema output\n41-- State: Single `workflow-state.yaml` in repo (beads-level simplicity)\n42-- Evaluator isolation: Separate workspace, no source code, Docker container for artifact\n43-- Docker: Required for evaluator but graceful degradation if missing (Journey 5)\n44-\n45-### Cross-Cutting Concerns\n--\n64-| Language | TypeScript (strict) | Existing project |\n65-| Build | tsup | Existing project |\n66-| Test | vitest (unit) + BATS (integration) | Existing project |\n67-| CLI | commander | Existing project |\n68-| YAML | yaml package | Existing project |\n69:| **New** | @anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk | Research — replaces bash spawn |\n70-\n71-**No starter template needed.** One new dependency added. Internals reworked.\n72-\n73-## Core Architectural Decisions\n74-\n--\n93-| Module | Responsibility | Key FRs |\n94-|--------|---------------|---------|\n95-| `workflow-parser` | Parse YAML, validate against JSON schema, resolve patches (embedded→user→project) | FR1-6, FR13-15 |\n96-| `agent-resolver` | Resolve agent config through patch chain, compile to SDK inline subagent definition | FR7-12 |\n97-| `workflow-engine` | Execute flow steps, manage iterations, handle `loop:` blocks, inject evaluator findings into retries | FR16-18, FR29-31 |\n98:| `agent-dispatch` | Call Agent SDK `query()`, manage sessions (fresh/continue), inject trace IDs | FR19-23 |\n99-| `evaluator` | Blind evaluator workspace setup, spawn, JSON verdict parsing | FR24-28 |\n100-| `circuit-breaker` | Score-based stagnation detection, score history tracking | FR32-35 |\n101-| `workflow-state` | Read/write workflow-state.yaml, crash recovery (resume from last completed task) | NFR6-8 |\n102-\n103-**Rationale:** 7 modules, each 100-200 LOC. Feedback loop (FR29-30) is part of `workflow-engine` — it's loop logic, not a separate concern. CLI commands (`init`, `run`, `validate`, `status`) are thin wrappers calling these modules. Observability (FR36-37) is a cross-cutting concern handled by trace ID injection in `agent-dispatch`, not a separate module.\n--\n110-/tmp/codeharness-verify-{runId}/\n111-  story-files/     # copied ACs from sprint\n112-  verdict/         # evaluator writes JSON verdict here\n113-```\n114-\n115:Engine copies story files to temp dir, spawns evaluator with `cwd` set to this directory. Agent SDK options enforce isolation:\n116-- `bare: true` — no plugins, hooks, MCP, memory\n117-- `disallowedTools: [\"Edit\", \"Write\"]` — read-only + execute only\n118-- `cwd: /tmp/codeharness-verify-{runId}` — no source code present\n119-\n120:**Rationale:** Simplest approach. Source isn't there because we never put it there. No git worktree complexity, no Docker-in-Docker. The Agent SDK's `cwd` + `disallowedTools` provide sufficient isolation.\n121-\n122:### AD3: Embedded Template Storage\n123-\n124-**Decision:** `templates/` directory in the npm package.\n125-\n126-```\n127-templates/\n--\n152-2. Resolve all referenced agents: same resolution chain → cache\n153-3. Run engine with cached configs — no file I/O during execution\n154-\n155-**Rationale:** Config files don't change during a run. Caching guarantees NFR2 (<200ms resolution) and eliminates repeated file system reads during long-running execution.\n156-\n157:### AD5: Evaluator Verdict Schema\n158-\n159:**Decision:** Structured JSON enforced by Agent SDK `jsonSchema` option.\n160-\n161-```typescript\n162-interface EvaluatorVerdict {\n163-  verdict: 'pass' | 'fail';\n164-  score: {\n--\n180-  evaluator_trace_id: string;\n181-  duration_seconds: number;\n182-}\n183-```\n184-\n185:**Rationale:** Replaces the 175-line proof document regex parser entirely. The Agent SDK validates the output against this schema — if the evaluator doesn't produce valid JSON, the SDK rejects it. Every AC verdict requires evidence (commands + output), enforcing the anti-leniency principle structurally.\n186-\n187-### Decision Impact Analysis\n188-\n189-**Implementation Sequence:**\n190-1. `workflow-state` — foundation for crash recovery, needed by everything\n--\n226-Project-level: `.codeharness/agents/`, `.codeharness/workflows/`.\n227-No alternative locations.\n228-\n229-### Format Patterns\n230-\n231:**Evaluator verdict:** JSON schema enforced (AD5). No alternative formats. Every AC requires `status`, `evidence.commands_run`, `evidence.output_observed`.\n232-\n233-**Workflow state:** YAML in `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml`. No JSON, no SQLite, no binary.\n234-\n235-**Resolved configs:** In-memory only. Never written to disk.\n236-\n--\n253-\n254-**State writes:** After EVERY task completion. Never batch. Never defer. Crash recovery guarantee.\n255-\n256-**Trace ID format:** `ch-{runId}-{iteration}-{taskName}` — deterministic, greppable. Example: `ch-abc123-3-verify`.\n257-\n258:**Session boundary enforcement:** `session: fresh` = new Agent SDK query with no resume/continue. No session reuse optimization across tasks.\n259-\n260-### Enforcement Guidelines\n261-\n262-**All agents implementing codeharness v2 MUST:**\n263-- Run `vitest run` before marking any module complete — 80%+ coverage\n264:- Use Agent SDK `query()` for all agent dispatch — never `execFileSync`\n265-- Write workflow-state.yaml after every task — never hold state only in memory\n266-- Use `bare: true` for all programmatic agent spawns\n267-\n268-**Anti-Patterns:**\n269-- Caching evaluator verdicts across iterations (each is full re-verification)\n--\n310-│   │   │\n311-│   │   │  # ── NEW MODULES (v2 architecture) ──\n312-│   │   ├── workflow-parser.ts             # YAML parse, schema validate, patch resolution\n313-│   │   ├── agent-resolver.ts             # Agent config resolution, SDK compilation\n314-│   │   ├── workflow-engine.ts            # Flow execution, loops, finding injection\n315:│   │   ├── agent-dispatch.ts             # Agent SDK query(), sessions, trace IDs\n316-│   │   ├── evaluator.ts                  # Blind evaluator workspace + spawn + verdict parsing\n317-│   │   ├── circuit-breaker.ts            # Score-based stagnation detection (TS rewrite)\n318-│   │   ├── workflow-state.ts             # State persistence, crash recovery (replaces state.ts)\n319-│   │   │\n320-│   │   │  # ── KEPT MODULES (existing, no changes) ──\n--\n486-codeharness run\n487-  → workflow-parser: load + resolve workflow YAML\n488-  → agent-resolver: resolve all referenced agents, cache\n489-  → workflow-engine: execute flow steps\n490-    → per-story tasks:\n491:        agent-dispatch: SDK query() → agent works → returns\n492-        workflow-state: write checkpoint\n493-    → per-run tasks (verify):\n494-        evaluator: setup workspace → agent-dispatch → parse verdict\n495-        workflow-state: write checkpoint + scores\n496-        circuit-breaker: evaluate stagnation\n--\n500-\n501-## Architecture Validation Results\n502-\n503-### Coherence Validation\n504-\n505:**Decision Compatibility:** All technology choices (Agent SDK + TypeScript + commander + yaml) are Node.js ecosystem, no conflicts. Agent SDK async generator + sequential engine execution are compatible. JSON schema validation consistent across workflow, agent, and verdict schemas.\n506-\n507-**Pattern Consistency:** kebab-case files + camelCase exports matches existing codebase. snake_case YAML keys is standard cross-language convention. Write-after-task state pattern aligns with crash recovery requirement.\n508-\n509-**Structure Alignment:** 7 modules in `src/lib/` with co-located tests matches existing structure. Templates in `templates/` matches existing distribution. `.codeharness/` for project config is clean separation from `.claude/`.\n510-\n--\n512-\n513-### Requirements Coverage\n514-\n515-**43 FRs:** All mapped to specific modules. No FR unaddressed.\n516-\n517:**18 NFRs:** All addressed — performance by caching, reliability by state persistence, integration by Agent SDK, code quality by project structure.\n518-\n519-**Minor gap:** Verdict schema needs `infrastructure_available: boolean` for graceful degradation when Docker is unavailable (Journey 5). Resolution: add the field.\n520-\n521-### Implementation Readiness\n522-"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015upEEv2DfZnR9xKiJz9ZsK","session_id":"84c2a87f-6818-4ede-b88c-dde16fd6e99b","uuid":"8152b11c-1b0f-45d1-99ba-edcd27d771df","timestamp":"2026-04-02T19:39:51.305Z"}
