{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RfTYqDmmASgcNTn6ZekU4H","type":"tool_result","content":"1350\t     *\n1351\t     * @example Custom prompt\n1352\t     * ```typescript\n1353\t     * systemPrompt: 'You are a helpful coding assistant.'\n1354\t     * ```\n1355\t     *\n1356\t     * @example Default with additions\n1357\t     * ```typescript\n1358\t     * systemPrompt: {\n1359\t     *   type: 'preset',\n1360\t     *   preset: 'claude_code',\n1361\t     *   append: 'Always explain your reasoning.'\n1362\t     * }\n1363\t     * ```\n1364\t     */\n1365\t    systemPrompt?: string | {\n1366\t        type: 'preset';\n1367\t        preset: 'claude_code';\n1368\t        append?: string;\n1369\t    };\n1370\t    /**\n1371\t     * Custom function to spawn the Claude Code process.\n1372\t     * Use this to run Claude Code in VMs, containers, or remote environments.\n1373\t     *\n1374\t     * When provided, this function is called instead of the default local spawn.\n1375\t     * The default behavior checks if the executable exists before spawning.\n1376\t     *\n1377\t     * @example\n1378\t     * ```typescript\n1379\t     * spawnClaudeCodeProcess: (options) => {\n1380\t     *   // Custom spawn logic for VM execution\n1381\t     *   // options contains: command, args, cwd, env, signal\n1382\t     *   return myVMProcess; // Must satisfy SpawnedProcess interface\n1383\t     * }\n1384\t     * ```\n1385\t     */\n1386\t    spawnClaudeCodeProcess?: (options: SpawnOptions) => SpawnedProcess;\n1387\t};\n1388\t\n1389\texport declare type OutputFormat = JsonSchemaOutputFormat;\n1390\t\n1391\texport declare type OutputFormatType = 'json_schema';\n1392\t\n1393\texport declare type PermissionBehavior = 'allow' | 'deny' | 'ask';\n1394\t\n1395\t/**\n1396\t * Classification of this permission decision for telemetry. SDK hosts that prompt users (desktop apps, IDEs) should set this to reflect what actually happened: user_temporary for allow-once, user_per