{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DmodJessUS9Zyp4CtHWrwe","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Code Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration\n**Tests:** 27 passed (27/27), 0 regressions in full suite (3833/3833)\n**Coverage:** agent-dispatch.ts at 100% statements, 100% lines, 100% functions, 97.22% branches\n**Overall coverage:** 96.63% (target: 90%) | All 154 files above 80% per-file floor\n**Story status:** updated to `verifying`\n\n### Issues Fixed (HIGH + MEDIUM)\n\n| # | Severity | Issue | Fix |\n|---|----------|-------|-----|\n| 1 | HIGH | Error tests used try/catch without `expect.assertions()` — if no throw, tests silently pass with 0 assertions | Added `expect.assertions(N)` to all 10 error tests |\n| 2 | HIGH | RATE_LIMIT test called `dispatchAgent` twice (once for `rejects.toThrow`, once in try/catch), wasting a mock call and risking false positives | Consolidated into single try/catch with `expect(err).toBeInstanceOf(DispatchError)` |\n| 3 | MEDIUM | No test verifying `permissionMode: 'bypassPermissions'` is passed to SDK (AC #1 bare mode enforcement) | Added test asserting both `permissionMode` and `allowDangerouslySkipPermissions` |\n| 4 | MEDIUM | Line 88 (message-based NETWORK classification via fetch/network/dns regex) was untested | Added test for `'fetch failed: network error'` message classification |\n| 5 | MEDIUM | Dead type in `systemPrompt` variable — union with `{ type: 'preset'; ... }` never used | Simplified to `string` type only |\n\n### Files Modified\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts` — removed dead type union (line 121)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/agent-dispatch.test.ts` — added `expect.assertions()` guards, fixed double-call pattern, added 2 new tests\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration.md` — status to `verifying`\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: 10 error classification tests lacked `expect.assertions()` — would silently pass if `dispatchAgent` stopped throwing\n- HIGH: RATE_LIMIT test invoked mock twice, masking potential issues with mock state\n- MEDIUM: `permissionMode: 'bypassPermissions'` (the SDK equivalent of \"bare: true\") was untested despite being a core AC\n- MEDIUM: Message-based NETWORK classification path was dead code from a coverage perspective\n- MEDIUM: Unused type branch in systemPrompt variable declaration\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `spawn` substring check in no-child_process test (line 437) is overly broad — would flag comments or variable names containing \"spawn\". Acceptable risk since the module is small.\n- `exec(` substring check similarly broad — would match `execute`, `execution`, etc.\n- Branch coverage at 97.22% — the `message.session_id` falsy branch (empty string session_id from SDK) is uncovered. Edge case unlikely in practice.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None below floor. All files pass 80% per-file minimum. Overall 96.63% exceeds 90% target.\n- The `session_id` falsy-but-present branch is the only uncovered path.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. Module boundaries are clean — no state imports, no child_process, no retry logic. SDK integration pattern is correct.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed inline.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 6, Edit: 4, Grep: 4, Glob: 2, Skill: 1, Write: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run` full suite (~20 lines), `npx vitest run --coverage` (~30 lines), `npx codeharness coverage` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none — each read/search served a distinct purpose"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2cd8cd34f1870f80 (use SendMessage with to: 'a2