{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019ouC78mRX5Y7M6Z7XZGRtH","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"84c2a87f-6818-4ede-b88c-dde16fd6e99b","uuid":"12cfb372-9882-49b1-8604-36a76ef6fb8f","timestamp":"2026-04-02T19:53:29.585Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"### 4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration — create-story (2026-04-02T19:28)","newString":"### 4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration — code-review (2026-04-02T19:50)\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- HIGH: 10 error tests lacked `expect.assertions()` — would silently pass if `dispatchAgent` stopped throwing\n- HIGH: RATE_LIMIT test invoked mock twice, masking potential issues with mock state\n- MEDIUM: `permissionMode: 'bypassPermissions'` (bare:true equivalent) was untested despite being a core AC\n- MEDIUM: Message-based NETWORK classification path was untested\n- MEDIUM: Unused type branch in systemPrompt variable declaration\n\n**Code quality issues NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `spawn`/`exec(` substring checks in no-child_process test are overly broad\n- Branch coverage at 97.22% — `session_id` falsy branch uncovered\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 6, Edit: 4, Grep: 4, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: vitest full suite (~20 lines), vitest coverage (~30 lines), codeharness coverage (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration — create-story (2026-04-02T19:28)","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-02 (Session 9)\n\n### 4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration — create-story (2026-04-02T19:28)\n\n- **Ambiguity: SDK API shape unknown.** `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` is not yet installed. Exact API surface (`query()` params, return types, error shapes) unknown. Story includes note that dev MUST check actual API.\n- **Workaround: Forward-compatible fields.** Added `sessionId` and `appendSystemPrompt` to `DispatchOptions` even though not used by this story — hooks for 4-2 and 4-3.\n- **Risk: Error classification heuristics** based on assumptions about HTTP status codes and Node.js error codes. May need adjustment once SDK installed.\n- **Observation: First new runtime dependency** (`@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`).\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 1, Read: 4, Grep: 7, Glob: 4, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: ls -la implementation-artifacts (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Two Glob calls for story files with different patterns could have been one broader search\n\n### 4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration — dev-story (2026-04-02T19:42)\n\n- **SDK API shape mismatch with story spec**: Story described `query()` as returning a result directly, but actual SDK returns `AsyncGenerator<SDKMessage>` that must be consumed. Implemented accordingly.\n- **`permissionMode: 'bypassPermissions'`**: Story didn't specify permission handling. Added `bypassPermissions` + `allowDangerouslySkipPermissions: true` since agents are programmatic. May need revisiting.\n- **Line 88 uncovered (91.66% branch coverage)**: One branch in `classifyError` for `fetch/network/dns` regex matching not tested. Minor gap.\n- **SDK is 45MB unpacked**: `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` adds significant package weight — bundles Claude Code CLI binary.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 12, Read: 5, Edit: 3, Grep: 4, Write: 2\n- Largest Bash outputs: npx vitest run (~500 lines), npm install (~10 lines), npx tsup (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 7 total reads\n- Redundant operations: vitest coverage ran twice — could have used single run with grep\n\n### 3-3-agent-resolver-module — create-story (2026-04-02T19:55)\n\n**Problems:** Workflow references `workflow.md` but actual file is `workflow.yaml` + `instructions.xml`. Used both to reconstruct full instructions.\n**Workarounds:** None significant. `SubagentDefinition` defined as plain TS interface since SDK not yet a dependency (story 4-1 adds it).\n**Risks:** AC #9 (<200ms perf) may be flaky on slow CI. Deep merge \"arrays replace\" strategy inferred not confirmed.\n**Observations:** All 10 ACs test-provable. Pure data transformation module.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 4, Read: 12, Grep: 3, Glob: 6, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: git diff --stat (~17 lines), git log --oneline (~10 lines), ls templates/agents/ (~9 lines)\n- Files read: 13 unique, 13 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 3-3-agent-resolver-module — dev-story (2026-04-02T23:10)\n\n- **Uncovered branches (lines 135-136, 145-149)**: Error paths inside `loadEmbeddedAgent` for YAML parse errors and schema validation failures on embedded templates. Since embedded templates are read-only shipped files, these branches are effectively dead code. Acceptable at 93.81% coverage.\n- **Type cast pattern**: `as unknown as ResolvedAgent` double-cast bypasses type safety. A runtime type guard would be cleaner but duplicates schema validation logic. Known trade-off.\n- **Pre-existing TS errors**: `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` has 2 unrelated TypeScript errors (lines 188, 200) predating this work.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 15\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 4, Edit: 4, Grep: 0, Write: 0, other: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage report (~140 lines), full test suite (~15 lines), tsc errors (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 4 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 3-3-agent-resolver-module — code-review (2026-04-02T23:18)\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- **HIGH** — Path traversal vulnerability: `resolveAgent()` accepted arbitrary strings, allowing `../../../etc/passwd` style inputs. Fixed with `validateName()` regex.\n- **HIGH** — `prompt_patches` not stripped during custom agent schema validation. Fixed.\n- **HIGH** — Mutation + redundant spread in return path. Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `loadPatch()` used for full custom agent files — semantic mismatch\n- Custom agent silently shadows embedded + patch chain (by design per AC #8)\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Lines 153-154, 163-167 (embedded template error paths) untested — defensive branches for corrupted templates\n- No integration test with real filesystem user home + project dir\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1, Write: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs: full test suite (~10 lines), coverage (~30 lines), first test run (~6 lines)\n- Files read: 9 unique, 10 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Two failed test runs attempting to mock named fs imports could have been avoided\n\n### 3-3-agent-resolver-module — verification (2026-04-02T23:30)\n\n- **Meta-gate failures:** `codeharness verify` flags coverage_met (100% target in story patch vs 94.05% actual — AC specifies 80%) and AGENTS.md staleness. These are harness-level gates, not AC failures.\n- **Pre-existing BATS failures:** Integration tests fail with exit 127 (command not found) — unrelated to story 3-3.\n- **Branch coverage:** 83.82% — defensive error paths for corrupted embedded templates are untested.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 1, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: npm test (~80 lines), vitest verbose (~80 lines), vitest coverage (~60 lines)\n- Files read: 1 unique, 1 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None significant\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":5,"newStart":1,"newLines":25,"lines":[" # Session Issues Log — 2026-04-02 (Session 9)"," ","+### 4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration — code-review (2026-04-02T19:50)","+","+**Bugs found and fixed:**","+- HIGH: 10 error tests lacked `expect.assertions()` — would silently pass if `dispatchAgent` stopped throwing","+- HIGH: RATE_LIMIT test invoked mock twice, masking potential issues with mock state","+- MEDIUM: `permissionMode: 'bypassPermissions'` (bare:true equivalent) was untested despite being a core AC","+- MEDIUM: Message-based NETWORK classification path was untested","+- MEDIUM: Unused type branch in systemPrompt variable declaration","+","+**Code quality issues NOT fixed (LOW):**","+- `spawn`/`exec(` substring checks in no-child_process test are overly broad","+- Branch coverage at 97.22% — `session_id` falsy branch uncovered","+","+## Token Report","+- Total tool calls: 21","+- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 6, Edit: 4, Grep: 4, Glob: 2, Skill: 1","+- Largest Bash outputs: vitest full suite (~20 lines), vitest coverage (~30 lines), codeharness coverage (~5 lines)","+- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads","+- Redundant operations: none","+"," ### 4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration — create-story (2026-04-02T19:28)"," "," - **Ambiguity: SDK API shape unknown.** `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` is not yet installed. Exact API surface (`query()` params, return types, error shapes) unknown. Story includes note that dev MUST check actual API."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
