{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q8cR2zGkFJz5yBNUTfaRSv","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-02 (Session 9)\n2\t\n3\t### 4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration — code-review (2026-04-02T19:50)\n4\t\n5\t**Bugs found and fixed:**\n6\t- HIGH: 10 error tests lacked `expect.assertions()` — would silently pass if `dispatchAgent` stopped throwing\n7\t- HIGH: RATE_LIMIT test invoked mock twice, masking potential issues with mock state\n8\t- MEDIUM: `permissionMode: 'bypassPermissions'` (bare:true equivalent) was untested despite being a core AC\n9\t- MEDIUM: Message-based NETWORK classification path was untested\n10\t- MEDIUM: Unused type branch in systemPrompt variable declaration\n11\t\n12\t**Code quality issues NOT fixed (LOW):**\n13\t- `spawn`/`exec(` substring checks in no-child_process test are overly broad\n14\t- Branch coverage at 97.22% — `session_id` falsy branch uncovered\n15\t\n16\t## Token Report\n17\t- Total tool calls: 21\n18\t- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 6, Edit: 4, Grep: 4, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n19\t- Largest Bash outputs: vitest full suite (~20 lines), vitest coverage (~30 lines), codeharness coverage (~5 lines)\n20\t- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads\n21\t- Redundant operations: none\n22\t\n23\t### 4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration — create-story (2026-04-02T19:28)\n24\t\n25\t- **Ambiguity: SDK API shape unknown.** `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` is not yet installed. Exact API surface (`query()` params, return types, error shapes) unknown. Story includes note that dev MUST check actual API.\n26\t- **Workaround: Forward-compatible fields.** Added `sessionId` and `appendSystemPrompt` to `DispatchOptions` even though not used by this story — hooks for 4-2 and 4-3.\n27\t- **Risk: Error classification heuristics** based on assumptions about HTTP status codes and Node.js error codes. May need adjustment once SDK installed.\n28\t- **Observation: First new runtime dependency** (`@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`).\n29\t\n30\t## Token Report\n31\t- Total tool calls: 16\n32\t- By tool: Bash: 1, Read: 4, Grep: 7, Glob: 4, Write: 1\n33\t- Largest Bash outputs: ls -la implementation-artifacts (~20 lines)\n34\t- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n35\t- Redundant operations: Two Glob calls for story files with different patterns could have been one broader search\n36\t\n37\t### 4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration — dev-story (2026-04-02T19:42)\n38\t\n39\t- **SDK API shape mismatch with story spec**: Story described `query()` as returning a result directly, but actual SDK returns `AsyncGenerator<SDKMessage>` that must be consumed. Implemented accordingly.\n40\t- **`permissionMode: 'bypassPermissions'`**: Story didn't specify permission handling. Added `bypassPermissions` + `allowDangerouslySkipPermissions: true` since agents are programmatic. May need revisiting.\n41\t- **Line 88 uncovered (91.66% branch coverage)**: One branch in `classifyError` for `fetch/network/dns` regex matching not tested. Minor gap.\n42\t- **SDK is 45MB unpacked**: `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` adds significant package weight — bundles Claude Code CLI binary.\n43\t\n44\t## Token Report\n45\t- Total tool calls: 21\n46\t- By tool: Bash: 12, Read: 5, Edit: 3, Grep: 4, Write: 2\n47\t- Largest Bash outputs: npx vitest run (~500 lines), npm install (~10 lines), npx tsup (~10 lines)\n48\t- Files read: 7 unique, 7 total reads\n49\t- Redundant operations: vitest coverage ran twice — could have used single run with grep\n50\t\n51\t### 3-3-agent-resolver-module — create-story (2026-04-02T19:55)\n52\t\n53\t**Problems:** Workflow references `workflow.md` but actual file is `workflow.yaml` + `instructions.xml`. Used both to reconstruct full instructions.\n54\t**Workarounds:** None significant. `SubagentDefinition` defined as plain TS interface since SDK not yet a dependency (story 4-1 adds it).\n55\t**Risks:** AC #9 (<200ms perf) may be flaky on slow CI. Deep merge \"arrays replace\" strategy inferred not confirmed.\n56\t**Observations:** All 10 ACs test-provable. Pure data transformation module.\n57\t\n58\t## Token Report\n59\t- Total tool calls: 19\n60\t- By tool: Bash: 4, Read: 12, Grep: 3, Glob: 6, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n61\t- Largest Bash outputs: git diff --stat (~17 lines), git log --oneline (~10 lines), ls templates/agents/ (~9 lines)\n62\t- Files read: 13 unique, 13 total reads\n63\t- Redundant operations: None\n64\t\n65\t### 3-3-agent-resolver-module — dev-story (2026-04-02T23:10)\n66\t\n67\t- **Uncovered branches (lines 135-136, 145-149)**: Error paths inside `loadEmbeddedAgent` for YAML parse errors and schema validation failures on embedded templates. Since embedded templates are read-only shipped files, these branches are effectively dead code. Acceptable at 93.81% coverage.\n68\t- **Type cast pattern**: `as unknown as ResolvedAgent` double-cast bypasses type safety. A runtime type guard would be cleaner but duplicates schema validation logic. Known trade-off.\n69\t- **Pre-existing TS errors**: `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` has 2 unrelated TypeScript errors (lines 188, 200) predating this work.\n70\t\n71\t## Token Report\n72\t- Total tool calls: 15\n73\t- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 4, Edit: 4, Grep: 0, Write: 0, other: 0\n74\t- Largest Bash outputs: coverage report (~140 lines), full test suite (~15 lines), tsc errors (~5 lines)\n75\t- Files read: 3 unique, 4 total reads\n76\t- Redundant operations: none\n77\t\n78\t### 3-3-agent-resolver-module — code-review (2026-04-02T23:18)\n79\t\n80\t**Bugs found and fixed:**\n81\t- **HIGH** — Path traversal vulnerability: `resolveAgent()` accepted arbitrary strings, allowing `../../../etc/passwd` style inputs. Fixed with `validateName()` regex.\n82\t- **HIGH** — `prompt_patches` not stripped during custom agent schema validation. Fixed.\n83\t- **HIGH** — Mutation + redundant spread in return path. Fixed.\n84\t\n85\t**Code quality issues NOT fixed (LOW):**\n86\t- `loadPatch()` used for full custom agent files — semantic mismatch\n87\t- Custom agent silently shadows embedded + patch chain (by design per AC #8)\n88\t\n89\t**Coverage gaps:**\n90\t- Lines 153-154, 163-167 (embedded template error paths) untested — defensive branches for corrupted templates\n91\t- No integration test with real filesystem user home + project dir\n92\t\n93\t## Token Report\n94\t- Total tool calls: 19\n95\t- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1, Write: 0\n96\t- Largest Bash outputs: full test suite (~10 lines), coverage (~30 lines), first test run (~6 lines)\n97\t- Files read: 9 unique, 10 total reads\n98\t- Redundant operations: Two failed test runs attempting to mock named fs imports could have been avoided\n99\t\n100\t### 3-3-agent-resolver-module — verification (2026-04-02T23:30)\n101\t\n102\t- **Meta-gate failures:** `codeharness verify` flags coverage_met (100% target in story patch vs 94.05% actual — AC specifies 80%) and AGENTS.md staleness. These are harness-level gates, not AC failures.\n103\t- **Pre-existing BATS failures:** Integration tests fail with exit 127 (command not found) — unrelated to story 3-3.\n104\t- **Branch coverage:** 83.82% — defensive error paths for corrupted embedded templates are untested.\n105\t\n106\t## Token Report\n107\t- Total tool calls: 12\n108\t- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 1, Write: 1\n109\t- Largest Bash outputs: npm test (~80 lines), vitest verbose (~80 lines), vitest coverage (~60 lines)\n110\t- Files read: 1 unique, 1 total reads\n111\t- Redundant operations: None significant\n112\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TLirBy5ewxwL6m96MPCs9Z","session_id":"84c2a87f-6818-4ede-b88c-dde16fd6e99b","uuid":"3f72c88d-4bff-4b1a-b063-de6852fe650a","timestamp":"2026-04-02T19:54:03.435Z"}
