{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014eE2hcThZGHdP2NDmQLZ4a","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-02\n2\t\n3\t## Session Summary\n4\t\n5\t**Date:** 2026-04-02\n6\t**Duration:** ~18 minutes (10:07 - 10:25 UTC)\n7\t**Stories attempted:** 1\n8\t**Stories completed:** 1\n9\t\n10\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome |\n11\t|-------|-----------|---------|\n12\t| 1-2-delete-ralph-loop-legacy-verification | code-review, verification | done |\n13\t\n14\tStory 1-1-delete-beads-integration was completed in an earlier session today (07:58 - 09:45 UTC). This session only handled the final review and verification of story 1-2.\n15\t\n16\t**Sprint progress after session:** Epic 1 stories 1-1 and 1-2 both `done`. Next up: 1-3-workflow-state-module.\n17\t\n18\t---\n19\t\n20\t## Issues Analysis\n21\t\n22\t### Categorized Issues from Session Log\n23\t\n24\t**Story Spec Errors (2)**\n25\t- `src/lib/state.ts` listed for deletion in AC #3, but has 14+ importers — would break the project. Dev agent correctly skipped it.\n26\t- `src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts` path in story spec was wrong — actual file was at `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts`.\n27\t\n28\t**Incomplete Cleanup (2)**\n29\t- HIGH: ralph/ directory not fully deleted on disk — remaining files (.call_count, .harness-prompt.md, state files, logs) caught by code review.\n30\t- MEDIUM: `package.json` `files` array still references `ralph/**/*.sh` and `ralph/AGENTS.md` — stale entries for deleted directory.\n31\t\n32\t**Test/Coverage Issues (1)**\n33\t- MEDIUM: `run.ts` coverage dropped to 67.44% (below 80% floor) after ralph removal. Code review added 7 tests to fix.\n34\t\n35\t**Stale References (3)**\n36\t- `dashboard-formatter.ts` comment leak referencing \"ralph\"\n37\t- `stats.ts` hardcoded `ralph/logs/` path — broken after deletion\n38\t- Multiple JSDoc comments still referenced ralph/beads (fixed in code review)\n39\t\n40\t**Process Issues (1)**\n41\t- Verification proof document had wrong format — had to be rewritten to match expected `## AC N: Title` format.\n42\t\n43\t### Severity Distribution\n44\t\n45\t| Severity | Count | Fixed? |\n46\t|----------|-------|--------|\n47\t| HIGH | 1 | Yes |\n48\t| MEDIUM | 3 | 2 fixed, 1 deferred (package.json stale entries) |\n49\t| LOW | 2 | Deferred (stubs, dead test suites) |\n50\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TLirBy5ewxwL6m96MPCs9Z","session_id":"84c2a87f-6818-4ede-b88c-dde16fd6e99b","uuid":"e2c4946e-c433-445a-a98e-ab06d2630cd5","timestamp":"2026-04-02T19:54:11.664Z"}
