{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Jz9bYrbt4P4qB4MLAvyF9D","type":"tool_result","content":"2090\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n2091\t\n2092\t### Patterns to Repeat\n2093\t\n2094\t1. **Code review on security-sensitive modules is non-negotiable.** The agent resolver accepts user-provided file paths and loads YAML from disk — path traversal was a real risk. The $3-4 review cost prevented a shipped vulnerability.\n2095\t2. **Deep merge modules need explicit array strategy documentation.** The \"arrays replace\" strategy was inferred, not confirmed. For the next deep-merge consumer (Epic 4 dispatch module), the strategy should be documented in the story spec.\n2096\t3. **Test-provable ACs continue to be the fastest path.** 10/10 ACs test-provable = mechanical verification. No subjective evaluation, no ambiguity.\n2097\t\n2098\t### Patterns to Avoid\n2099\t\n2100\t1. **Don't retry rate limits immediately.** Ralph attempted 3 retries in 2 minutes. Should detect the \"rate limit\" response pattern and wait until the stated reset time.\n2101\t2. **Don't carry unfixed tooling bugs across 7+ sessions.** `codeharness stats` has been broken all day. Either fix it or remove it from the retro workflow.\n2102\t3. **Don't use 100% coverage in story patches when AC says 80%.** The mismatch causes false positives in `codeharness verify` and wastes verification cycles investigating non-issues.\n2103\t\n2104\t---\n2105\t\n2106\t## 7. Action Items\n2107\t\n2108\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner | Status |\n2109\t|---|--------|----------|-------|--------|\n2110\t| 1 | Fix ralph rate-limit retry logic — detect \"rate limit\" response and wait until reset time | HIGH | dev | NEW |\n2111\t| 2 | Fix `codeharness stats` to work without session-logs/ directory | HIGH | dev | Carried x7 |\n2112\t| 3 | Fix `codeharness verify` to use AC-specified coverage threshold, not story patch target | MEDIUM | dev | NEW |\n2113\t| 4 | Document deep-merge array strategy (replace vs append) in architecture docs | MEDIUM | docs | NEW |\n2114\t| 5 | Fix pre-existing TS errors in `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` (lines 188, 200) | LOW | dev | NEW |\n2115\t| 6 | Fix pre-existing BATS integration test failures (exit 127) | LOW | dev | Carried |\n2116\t| 7 | Begin Epic 4: next story is 4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration | -- | sprint | Next session |\n2117\t\n2118\t---\n2119\t\n2120\t**Session 10 verdict:** Story 3-3 completed and Epic 3 is done. The code review justified its cost by catching 3 HIGH security bugs (path traversal, prompt_patches leak, mutation). The rate limit caused a 2-hour wall-clock delay and made this the most expensive single story of the day at ~$9-10, but active compute time was only ~35 minutes with 65 tool calls — comparable to average sessions. Cumulative day total: ~$55-58 for 11 stories across 3 epics. The `codeharness stats` bug has now been carried for 7 sessions without a fix — it should be prioritized before the next sprint.\n2121\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TLirBy5ewxwL6m96MPCs9Z","session_id":"84c2a87f-6818-4ede-b88c-dde16fd6e99b","uuid":"5a0028fa-e2ef-47d4-865a-f0e6431ae80d","timestamp":"2026-04-02T19:54:17.786Z"}
